@node Intro   "Introduction"
@next Install
@toc  Main
AC97 Mixer 2.1                                             01-Sep-2002





     Excited about the new Amithlon Amiga emulator I had to write this
     program to use more of the Audio features of PC soundcards.
     
     Requirements: 

       Kickstart/WB   : Amithlon with OS 3.1/3.5
       Other software : MUI
       Other hardware : ES1371/CT5880 or VIA VT82C686 or EMU10K based
                        soundcard or Maestro2/3

     Note:

       Since I don't have onboard sound or any other soundcard, please
       report  all errors  regarding VIA or SB Live immediately.  I'll
       provide a debug version as soon as possible.


     Next supported card:

       Will see which AHI drivers come next.


@endnode

@node Install "Installation"
@next Use
@toc  Main
AC97 Mixer 2.1                                             01-Sep-2002





     The  installation is very simple.  I think, that I don't need the
     Installer for these files. The AC97Mixer program should be copied
     into the WBStartup directory which is the best place for it.
     
     The program  opens a  MUI application window with all the sliders
     which control the SB 128 PCI volume and balance settings.


     @{b}Tooltypes@{ub} -------------------------------------------------------

        CX_POPUP   : If "YES" then the GUI appears at startup time.

        SAVEONEXIT : If "YES" the mixer settings are written to
                     ENVARC:ac97.prefs

        NOCONTEXT  : Disables the context menu with this tooltype.

        DEBUG      : Writes debug messages to trap bugs
                    
@endnode

@node Use "Usage"
@next History
@toc  Main
AC97 Mixer 2.1                                             01-Sep-2002





     @{b}Balance@{ub} ---------------------------------------------------------

     These sliders  control the balance of the  selected channel. This
     function is not working correctly if you move the slider too fast


     @{b}Mixer@{ub} -----------------------------------------------------------

     These sliders control all the output  levels for Master, CD, AUX,
     PCM, LINE IN, MIC, CENTER, and SURROUND (if supported).

     You can  hide/show  each  mixer by  using the  right mouse button
     within  the  mixer window.  These  settings  will be saved if the
     SAVE_EXIT tooltype is set to YES.


     @{b}Mute@{ub} ------------------------------------------------------------

     If the checkmark gadget is checked the channel will be muted. The
     original volume values are preserved.


     @{b}20dB@{ub} ------------------------------------------------------------

     If the checkmark gadget enables the microphone pre-amplifier.


     @{b}3D@{ub} --------------------------------------------------------------

     Some codecs support some  form of 3D stereo enhancement. With the
     center  and  depth slider  you  can manipulate these values. This
     works not  always as expected. On my SB 128 PCI the center slider
     shows no effect.


     @{b}AREXX@{ub}

     An Arexx port  has been activated in version 1.7. The Port to use
     is SBMIX.1 The Arexx interface only controls the first sound card
     in the list. There are 4 commands implemented so far:


     @{b}CARD@{ub} ------------------------------------------------------------

     CARD index

       Activates  one of  the detected sound cards. The index value is
       same as the radio button number starting with '0'.


     @{b}MUTE@{ub} ------------------------------------------------------------

     MUTE channel TRUE|FALSE

       Mute or unmute a channel. Channel can be set to MASTER, CD, AUX,
       PCM, MIC, or LINE.


     @{b}GETVOL@{ub}

     GETVOL channel

       Gets the  volume and  mute status  for a channel. Channel can be
       set to MASTER, CD, AUX, PCM, MIC, or LINE.

       The result string shows the channel volume and TRUE or FALSE for
       the status of the mute gadget.


     @{b}SETVOL@{ub}

     SETVOL channel value

       Sets the volume for a channel. Channel can be set to MASTER, CD,
       AUX, PCM, MIC, or LINE.

       The  value for volume  ranges from 0 TO 31,  where 31 means full
       volume and 0 silence.


@endnode

@node History "History and Future of ToccataMixer"
@next Author
@toc  Main
AC97 Mixer 2.1                                             01-Sep-2002





     (A)dded (R)emoved (F)ixed (I)nfo          

     V 1.0....... 01-Jan-2002  initial release

     V 1.1....... 03-Jan-2002  (A) .... 3D stereo enhancement support

     V 1.2....... 07-Jan-2002  (A) .... LINE IN and MIC
                               (F) .... master resolution can be $3F
                               (F) .... volume changes if balance is not 0

     V 1.3....... 09-Jan-2002  (F) .... codec now gets initialized
                               (A) .... mixer settings are saved and restored

     V 1.4....... 19-Jan-2002  (F) .... additional init for ES1370 and ES1371

     V 1.5....... 27-Jan-2002  (A) .... MIC preamp + 20dB
                               (I) .... 3D sliders are only shown if CODEC has
                                        3D enhancement capabilities

     V 1.6....... 01-Mar-2002  (A) .... context menu to hide/show selected sliders

     V 1.61...... 02-Mar-2002  (F) .... bugfixes

     V 1.7....... 28-Apr-2002  (A) .... ARexx commands MUTE and SETVOL

     V 1.71...... 30-Apr-2002  (F) .... mastervolume didn't work correctly with
                                        codecs that have 6 bit volume resolution

     V 1.72...... 01-May-2002  (F) .... debug messages removed

     V 1.8....... 05-May-2002  (A) .... surround and center volume

     V 1.81......    May-2002  internal version

     V 1.82...... 20-May-2002  (A) .... ARexx command GETVOL
                               (F) .... closing the window now iconifies
                               (F) .... about window shows version

     V 1.83...... 30-May-2002  (F) .... mute via ARexx set full master volume

     V 1.9....... 16-Jun-2002  (A) .... VIA support

     V 1.91...... 26-Jun-2002  (F) .... multiple balance changes mute sound

     V 2.0....... 29-Jun-2002  (A) .... EMU10K support (SB live)

                  06-Jul-2002  (A) .... EMU10K support (Audigy)

     V 2.1....... 01-Sep-2002  (A) .... ESS1968 support (Maestro)


     @{b}Future@{ub} ----------------------------------------------------------

     * locale support
     * more cards, more features


     @{b}Known bugs@{ub} ------------------------------------------------------

     * mixer/MUI prefs crashes at start with faulty MUI installations


